    "text": "The LSOG continuous probability map can be thresholded at a specific probability value to create a binary map for direct comparison with the discrete LiDAR classification.",
    "topic": "thresholding for comparability"
  },
  {
    "text": "Direct comparison between a continuous probability map and a discrete classification map requires a defined conversion rule to avoid confounding map accuracy with classification threshold choice.",
    "topic": "meaningfulness of direct comparison"
  },
  {
    "text": "The pixel resolution and spatial alignment between the 10 m LSOG product and the Hagan et al. (2026) LiDAR map must be explicitly harmonized before any comparison.",
    "topic": "spatial harmonization"
  },
  {
    "text": "A validation protocol that uses the LiDAR map as reference data against the LSOG probability output without discretization can be conducted using probabilistic accuracy metrics like Brier score or AUC.",
    "topic": "alternative validation approach"
  }
